{0 A new home for the Ocsigen blog}

@author The Ocsigen team

The Ocsigen blog is back, and it is now built like the rest of the Ocsigen
website: with {{:/wodoc/}wodoc}, our odoc-based static site generator. Each post
is a plain [.mld] file — the same lightweight markup we use for the manuals and
the API documentation — so writing an article is just adding a file.

{1 How it works}

A post lives in [doc/blog/posts/] and is named [YYYY-MM-DD-slug.mld]: the date in
the file name is its publication date, and wodoc lists the posts newest first,
both in the navigation on the left and on this page. The author comes from the
standard odoc [@author] tag.

The feed at [/feed.xml] is generated from the same sources, so it keeps working
for the OCaml Planet aggregator exactly as before.
